                <note rend="inline" type="source">File 838.77/102.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My telegram of September 25. The Haitian Government has today served notice of
                    foreclosure on the National Railroad Company of Haiti for non-compliance with
                    Article 11 of the railroad contract and given notice of the adjudication of the
                    property on December 28. The Haitian Government has also notified claim for
                    damages caused the Government and public by the suspension of operation, and has
                    appointed an arbitrator on its part for examination of this last claim.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
